Election of 2014 in Värmlands län

Martin

2018-08-29

The 2014 Riksdag election

This is a presentation of the 2014 election to the national parliament, Riksdagen, in Sweden and how the people of the county of Värmland voted. Värmland is divided in 176 election districts with approximatly 1.000 voters in each. This is the voter’s turnout for every district:

Party support in Värmland

There are eight parties in the Swedish parliament. These maps show the support for each of them in the last election.
